      <section class="panel math-list-section-panel" aria-labelledby="math-list-depth-title">
        <div class="math-list-section-head">
          <div>
            <p class="math-list-section-kicker">Depth</p>
            <h2 id="math-list-depth-title" class="math-list-heading">Concept Guides Students Search For</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="math-list-depth-grid">
          <article class="math-list-depth-item">
            <h3>What is a quadratic equation?</h3>
            <p>A quadratic equation has the form ax² + bx + c = 0, where a is not zero. Students solve these using factoring or the quadratic formula. Use our <a href="quadratic-solver.html">quadratic equation solver</a> when you want instant roots plus discriminant context.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="math-list-depth-item">
            <h3>How do you solve equations step by step?</h3>
            <p>To solve equations, isolate x using inverse operations: add/subtract first, then multiply/divide. For multi-step expressions, simplify both sides before isolating x. Try the <a href="solver.html">equation solver</a> to compare your steps with a final result.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="math-list-depth-item">
            <h3>Why students use math calculators</h3>
            <p>Math calculators help students check accuracy, see patterns, and practice faster. The best use is learning-focused: solve manually, verify with a calculator, and then quiz yourself in <a href="quiz.html">Live Quiz</a> or <a href="premade-quiz.html">Premade Quiz</a>.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

