      <section class="panel math-list-section-panel math-list-section-panel-overview" aria-label="Math topics list">
        <div class="math-list-section-head">
          <div>
            <p class="math-list-section-kicker" data-i18n="mathlist.kickerCoverage">Coverage map</p>
            <h2 class="math-list-heading" data-i18n="mathlist.topicsTitle">Topics You Practice</h2>
            <p class="math-list-section-text" data-i18n="mathlist.coverageText">A quick overview of the kinds of equations and problem types available across the site.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul class="math-topic-list math-topic-list-rich">
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic1">Solving equations like x + 3 = 10</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic2">Two-step equations like 2x - 5 = 17</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic3">Equations with brackets like 3(x + 2) = 18</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic4">Quadratic equations like x^2 = 16</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic5">Understanding positive and negative roots</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic6">Multiple choice checking and retry practice</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic7">Step-by-step explanation reading</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic8">Visual equation balance logic</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic9">Positive exponent equations like 5^3 = x</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic10">Negative exponent equations and reciprocal logic</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic11">Square-root equations like sqrt(x + a) = b</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic12">Percentage equations with increases and decreases</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic13">Systems of equations with two unknowns</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic14">Geometry equations with perimeter, area, angles, and Pythagorean setup</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic15">Probability equations using fractions, percentages, and outcome ratios</li>
          <li data-i18n="mathlist.topic16">Zero exponent rules and equations like a^(x + b) = 1</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="panel math-list-section-panel" aria-labelledby="math-list-faq-title">
        <div class="math-list-section-head">
          <div>
            <p class="math-list-section-kicker">FAQ</p>
            <h2 id="math-list-faq-title" class="math-list-heading">Common Student Questions</h2>
            <p class="math-list-section-text">These quick answers help students choose the right tool and improve math practice efficiency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="math-list-faq-grid">
          <article class="math-list-faq-item">
            <h3>What is the best free online math calculator for equations?</h3>
            <p>Start with the <a href="solver.html">Equation Solver</a> for general equations, then use the <a href="quadratic-solver.html">Quadratic Equation Solver</a> for ax² + bx + c = 0 problems.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="math-list-faq-item">
            <h3>Where can I calculate fractions and percentages?</h3>
            <p>Use the <a href="fraction-calculator.html">Fraction Calculator</a> for operations and simplification, and the <a href="percentage-calculator.html">Percentage Calculator</a> for percent-of, ratio-percent, and percent change.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="math-list-faq-item">
            <h3>How should I practice math topics before a test?</h3>
            <p>Pick a topic in <a href="premade/all-topics.html">All Topics</a>, then quiz in <a href="premade-quiz.html">Premade Quiz</a>, and finish in <a href="test-me.html">Test Me</a> to revisit mistakes.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <div id="site-footer-mount"></div>
    <script>
      (function () {
        var btn = document.getElementById('quickLinearBtn');
        var msg = document.getElementById('quickLinearMessage');
        var box = document.getElementById('quickLinearResult');

        function fmt(n) {
          var rounded = Math.round(n * 1e10) / 1e10;
          return String(rounded);
        }

        if (!btn || !msg || !box) {
          return;
        }

        btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
          var a = parseFloat(document.getElementById('quickA').value);
          var b = parseFloat(document.getElementById('quickB').value);
          var c = parseFloat(document.getElementById('quickC').value);

          msg.textContent = '';
          box.innerHTML = '';
          box.classList.remove('is-visible');

          if (isNaN(a) || isNaN(b) || isNaN(c)) {
            msg.textContent = 'Enter valid numbers for a, b, and c.';
            return;
          }

          if (a === 0) {
            msg.textContent = 'a cannot be 0 in ax + b = c.';
            return;
          }

          var x = (c - b) / a;
          box.innerHTML = '<strong>Equation:</strong> ' + fmt(a) + 'x + ' + fmt(b) + ' = ' + fmt(c) + '<br>'
            + '<strong>Step 1:</strong> ' + fmt(a) + 'x = ' + fmt(c) + ' - ' + fmt(b) + ' = ' + fmt(c - b) + '<br>'
            + '<strong>Step 2:</strong> x = ' + fmt(c - b) + ' / ' + fmt(a) + '<br><br>'
            + '<strong>Answer:</strong> x = ' + fmt(x);
          box.classList.add('is-visible');
        });
      })();
    </script>
    <script src="Menu/menu.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
